Vice President Joe Biden spoke with Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko about various issues. They discussed the Rada's adoption of implementing measures for the law on special status for certain areas of eastern Ukraine, as called for in the Minsk agreements. They also talked about the upcoming multinational training program for Ukraine's National Guard, which the United States will support. Both leaders agreed that sanctions on Russia should be tied to the full implementation of the Minsk agreements. They also emphasized the need for the international community to increase the costs to Russia if it continues to fuel violence and instability in Ukraine.